Chashme Buddoor is a 1981 romantic comedy film starring Farooq Shaikh, Deepti Naval, Rakesh Bedi, Ravi Baswani and Saeed Jaffrey. The film is directed by Sai Paranjpye and produced by Gul Anand. The film is about three students; Siddharth (Farooq Shaikh), Omi (Rakesh Bedi) and Jai (Ravi Baswani) at Delhi University, who don't go home during summer vacation and how a girl Neha (Deepti Naval) comes in their life. 

David Dhawan is coming out with a remake of this movie with Ali Zafar, Taapsee Pannu, Divyendu Sharma, Siddharth Narayan and Rishi Kapoor in lead roles previously played by Farooq Shaikh, Deepti Naval, Rakesh Bedi, Ravi Baswani and Saeed Jaffrey.

This movie has some melodious songs :
1.Kahan se aaye badra - Yesudas &amp; Haimanti Shukla.
